    <h3><a id="links">Links section: Link to a paragraph on the same page</a></h3>
      To make a link to a paragraph or part in you webpage (on the same page) you can do the following:
      &lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name="me"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;paragraph title&lt;/h3&gt; (for Rails you have to use 'id' instead of 'name')
      this you put at the start of the part which you want to link to.
      You put the related link on top (or in navbar) of your web page you can get in one click to this section.
      So you will have to make a link on top of your page like so: &lt;a href="#me">Me section&lt;/a&gt;
  </pre>

